transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, John. My name is Kyle Bean. How are you doing today?

Speaker 1: I'm doing well. What can I do for you?

Speaker 2: I was actually calling because I've noticed that another payment was taken out for the subscription,

Speaker 1: which I've emailed and asked for it to be canceled before, and apparently it wasn't.

Speaker 2: So I need to make sure that it gets canceled out because I don't need it no longer.

Speaker 1: Okay. Can I get your zip code, please?

Speaker 2: Zip code? I don't remember what I had listed on there. I think it's 37331.

Speaker 1: How about your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 10-22-1985.

Speaker 1: I see your email, sir. We replied to you telling you you had to call, so that's why it wasn't done.

Speaker 2: I can take care of it now. We'll close out the account for good, though. That's what you want?

Speaker 1: Yeah. Will it continue because it's in the pharmacy process?

Speaker 2: Will it still cancel it out and be refunded?

Speaker 1: That one I have to check on.

Speaker 2: You can still get your money back on the one that's at the pharmacy, even if it's shipped.

Speaker 1: You just would have to return it when it gets to you, but I can cancel the future order, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So I'll check with the pharmacy on the other one, and I can let you know once I get a word back from them.

Speaker 2: Well, we'll do it this way. We'll let this one go.

Speaker 1: I just need to make sure that the address was updated when I did it.

Speaker 2: We have 301 First Street.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I'll go ahead and have this one sent out.

Speaker 2: I'll just have it for future references, but from here on, I'll just have it canceled out.

Speaker 1: Okay, Kyle. Then we're all set. We're squared away on our side.

Speaker 2: All right. I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Have a good day, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay. Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
